MXene (V2C)-based nanozymes were constructed with theranostic potential for treating ischemic stroke; these nanozymes exhibited excellent capabilities to exert neuroprotection effects by scavenging ROS toward ischemic stroke (Fig. 6) [72]. The MXenes fabricated via etching and delamination processes demonstrated the inherent multiple enzyme-mimicking features and excellent antioxidative capabilities to catalyze toxic/harmful O2·-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
